Make sure your `maven-surefire-plugin` is configured appropriately as:

    &lt;plugin&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;2.19.1&lt;/version&gt; &lt;!-- Specific due to memory leak in 2.20 --&gt;
        &lt;dependencies&gt;
             &lt;!--Custom provider and engine for Junit 5 to surefire--&gt;
             &lt;dependency&gt;
                 &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.platform&lt;/groupId&gt;
                 &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-platform-surefire-provider&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                 &lt;version&gt;1.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
             &lt;/dependency&gt;
             &lt;dependency&gt;
                 &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
                 &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                 &lt;version&gt;5.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
             &lt;/dependency&gt;
         &lt;/dependencies&gt;
         &lt;configuration&gt;
             &lt;argLine&gt;${argLine}&lt;/argLine&gt;
         &lt;/configuration&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

and you don&#39;t need the engine as dependencies, so you can remove this from your `&lt;dependencies&gt;` tag :-

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.junit.jupiter&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter-engine&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;5.0.1&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;


***Note***: The official documentation of the Junit5 about [running tests with maven](http://junit.org/junit5/docs/current/user-guide/#running-tests-build-maven) specifies using surefire 2.19.1 due to a memory leak in the 2.20 release version of the plugin.

